Universal care hospital, overwhelmed. If you are a guard, I recommend going during the time of least demand at the entrance, that happens between 7 am to 10 am more or less,
I come from several days of very high fever, they have treated me for 10 points, they have not found the reason but they are doing new tests on me, I feel cared for, thanks to the Catalan public health

snippet:
I left the hospital humiliated and condescended after being deferred treatment for accidental HIV exposure. Despite explaining that I needed treatment before a long series of flights, the infectious disease specialist deliberately refused to give me the Post exposure prophylaxis on time. The rather rude mediator said it was “my problem” that I could not wait for 4 hours to be seen. This is my worst experience ever at an Emergency room, all because I said I could not afford it (I’m a student).

It is already unbelievable that they let me leave untreated even after exposure. What’s downright criminal is that they subtly threatened for me through a lot of strong-arming and aggressive behaviour- just to avoid spending money on PEP medicine.

Is the Spanish medical system this flawed, even though they pretend to be concerned about public health?
user.name: Kush B
